				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>itchyban wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">%M is the pet.
<br />

<br />
I recall, from a looooong time ago, trying
<br />

<br />
/assist %M
<br />

<br />
in a hotkey, but it seemed that somehow it got stuck on my "first" pet's name and didn't update when I had subsequent pets in a play session. I haven't checked to see if that approach is still "buggy" these days.
<br />

<br />
F1 selects yourself, then toggles between you and your pet.
<br />

<br />
My "assist pet" "hotkey" is [F1] [F1] [nomal assist hotkey]</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes.  When you create the macro, you can put /assist %m as a line.  If you ever go back later and edit the macro, you can see that EQ did a subsutition of the pet name and your macro line is now /assist [pet name when macro created].
<br />

<br />
/pet target /assist is much prefered.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
